48:03.138 --> 48:09.848
Of course, it's an agricultural environment that they're familiar with and also grounded would be a foundational construction metaphor.

48:10.589 --> 48:18.701
And so as they're walking and through Ephesus, they would see the temple of Artemis and all of these columns and incredible things that Caesar and others had built.

48:19.222 --> 48:23.308
And when Paul says that grounded, that would be, in their mind, foundation.

48:24.430 --> 48:28.516
How can I be sustained that's agricultural, rooted?

48:28.536 --> 48:30.559
How can I grow and be sustained?

48:30.899 --> 48:32.722
And how can I have a firm foundation?

48:32.898 --> 48:34.560
So in their mind, they're thinking this.

48:34.620 --> 48:37.705
And so when Paul says, this is found in the love of God.

48:38.426 --> 48:44.755
